The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Peerless mutual next year
                                                                                                               Peerless mutual next year
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Calcutta, April 28: Peerless General Finance amp; Investment Company (PGFI) plans to launch its first mutual fund scheme in the first quarter of the next year.         
	Jayanta Roy, director (financial products distribution), PGFI, today said, We have got Sebis in-principle go-ahead to set up an asset management company for mutual fund business. It will take us another six months to get the final approval from the regulator. If we get the final nod by November, we shall be able to launch our first mutual fund scheme early next year.        
	According to Roy, the asset management company will be set up as a joint venture, preferably with a foreign partner.         
	Well start scouting for a joint venture partner, Roy said. As of now, our aim is to get a foreign company on board, he added.        
	We are in the midst of appointing a CEO for the asset management company, he said. It is learnt that ex-ICICI Prudential Mutual Fund executive Akshay Gupta has been selected for the top job.         
	The first board meeting of the firm will be held on May 5.         
	PGFI today signed an agreement with Max New York Life to sell the latters Max Vijay policies through its existing 3-year-old corporate agency tie-up.                                                                                                                                        
